.SH NAME
exOS \- exoterik_OS: a holographic bare-metal OS derived via exoteric linguistic synthesis
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./run.sh
.RB [ \-\-serial ]
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B exoterik_OS
is a bare-metal x86_64 operating system written in Rust (no_std) that operationalises the
Imscribing Grammar's 12-primitive type lattice as a functioning kernel type system.
It boots via UEFI OVMF and runs on QEMU.
.PP
The OS is derived from the component-wise MEET (structural floor) of five ancient writing
systems: Hebrew, Sanskrit Varnamala, Egyptian hieroglyphs, Sumerian cuneiform, and Basque
ergative-absolutive grammar.  Every kernel object carries an ALEPH type \(em one 12-primitive
tuple drawn from or inferred via the 22-letter Hebrew lattice \(em and four type gates
constrain real kernel subsystems: the scheduler, memory allocator, filesystem, and IPC.
.PP
Processes run as real ring-0 tasks on individually allocated 16\~KB kernel stacks.
Context switching is performed by a hand-written assembly routine
.RB ( context_switch_asm )
that saves and restores callee-saved registers and swaps RSP via a stable per-process slot in
.BR RSP_TABLE .
The PIT timer fires at \(ap18\~Hz and sets a preemption flag; the actual CPU switch is
deferred to cooperative yield points inside each process, avoiding IRET-frame corruption.
.
