.SH TYPE GATES
Four subsystems are constrained by ALEPH types at runtime.
.SS IPC Distance Gate
.B ipc.rs
\(em \fBcheck_grammar_gate()\fP, \fBis_type_valid()\fP
.PP
Structural distance d(source, target):
.RS
.IP "d < 0.5" 12
transparent \(em structurally identical, unrestricted
.IP "d < 1.5" 12
near-grounded \(em viable IPC
.IP "d \(>= 1.5" 12
aspirational \(em requires a vav-cast witness (mediating O_1+ type within 1.5 of both ends)
.RE
.PP
Broadcast delivery additionally requires the source's interaction-grammar primitive
\(*G\~\(>=\~3 (\fB\(*G_broad\fP).
Sources with \(*G\~=\~2 (\fB\(*G_seq\fP) are point-to-point only.
.SS Omega-Gate (Memory)
.B memory.rs
\(em \fBallocate_for()\fP, \fBcan_allocate_for()\fP
.PP
An object's \(*W (protection) must be \(>= the required \(*W of the articulation depth:
.RS
.IP "Velar / Palatal" 14
\(*W_Z (2) required
.IP "Retroflex" 14
\(*W_Z2 (1) required
.IP "Dental / Bilabial" 14
\(*W_0 (0) \(em unprotected
.RE
.PP
Additionally, \(*S_1:1 (Exclusive) objects are restricted to Velar depth only.
.SS Tier-Gate (Scheduler)
.B scheduler.rs
\(em \fBspawn_type_safe()\fP
.PP
Five axioms are enforced before queuing a process:
.RS
.IP "Ç_trap / Ç_MBL" 4
Kinetically frozen \(em cannot be scheduled under any conditions.
.IP "P-596 (\(sy_EP)" 4
Exceptional-point criticality absorbs the self-modeling loop (C=0).
Spawn is rejected.
.IP "O_0 ergative" 4
A subcritical process with transitive targets (non-empty pcb.targets) is rejected:
no self-modeling loop to sustain transitivity.
.IP "Frobenius F-1" 4
An O_\(if process must satisfy \(*m\(ci\(*d\~=\~id: parity index\~=\~4 AND phi index\~=\~1.
Violation is rejected.
.IP "\(*S quota" 4
\(*S_1:1 resources permit only one holder; \(*S_n:n pools have capacity 8.
Spawn that exceeds the quota is rejected.
.RE
.SS Phi-Gate (Filesystem)
.B filesystem.rs
\(em \fBnavigate_to_type_safe()\fP
.PP
Sefirot layers Keter through Gevurah (depth 0\(en5) require the accessing object to have
criticality \(*F_c (phi index\~\(>=\~1).
Sub-critical objects (Driver, Service without \(*F_c) are denied above Gevurah.
.
.SH PROCESS EXECUTION MODEL
.SS Spawning a Real Process
.nf
ProcessControlBlock::spawn_ring0(id, obj, entry_fn, priority)
.fi
.PP
Allocates a 16\~KB kernel stack via the global heap allocator.
Writes the initial saved-register frame at the top of the stack:
.nf

  [top \- 8]   entry_fn   <- ret address; jumped to on first schedule
  [top \- 16]  0          <- rbp
  [top \- 24]  0          <- rbx
  [top \- 32]  0          <- r12
  [top \- 40]  0          <- r13
  [top \- 48]  0          <- r14
  [top \- 56]  0          <- r15  <- initial RSP stored here

.fi
Assigns a slot in
.B RSP_TABLE[MAX_PROCS]
(static array; slots have stable addresses for the process lifetime).
.SS Context Switch
.nf
context_switch_asm(old_rsp_ptr: *mut u64, new_rsp: u64)
.fi
.PP
Assembly routine (global_asm!):
.nf

  push rbp; push rbx; push r12; push r13; push r14; push r15
  mov [rdi], rsp        ; save RSP into RSP_TABLE[old_slot]
  mov rsp, rsi          ; load RSP from RSP_TABLE[new_slot]
  pop r15; pop r14; pop r13; pop r12; pop rbx; pop rbp
  ret                   ; jumps to saved return address on new stack

.fi
Only invoked when both the outgoing and incoming process have real stacks (proc_slot > 0).
Legacy test PCBs fall back to a data-structure-only swap.
.SS Preemption Protocol
The PIT timer fires at \(ap18\~Hz.
.B timer_handler
calls
.BR scheduler::on_timer_tick() ,
which increments the running process's tick counter and sets
.B needs_preempt = true
when the time slice (18 ticks \(ap 1 second) expires.
.PP
Processes check
.B global_check_preempt()
at cooperative yield points (e.g. after each work unit in the holographic monitor loop).
The actual context switch happens in process context, not inside the interrupt frame.
This avoids corruption of the IRET state.
.SS Stoichiometric Quotas
.nf
stoichiometry::register(resource_id, mode, capacity)
stoichiometry::acquire(resource_id, pid) -> Result<(), &str>
stoichiometry::release(resource_id, pid)
stoichiometry::occupancy(resource_id) -> Option<(Stoichiometry, u64, u64)>
.fi
.PP
.TS
tab(@) allbox;
lb lb lb
l l l.
Mode@Primitive index@Enforcement
\(*S_1:1 (Exclusive)@0@One holder only; second acquire returns Err
\(*S_n:n (Homogeneous)@1@Pool of capacity 8; acquire fails when full
\(*S_n:m (Heterogeneous)@2@No hard cap; occupancy tracked for diagnostics
.TE
