.SH BOOT SEQUENCE
.TP
.B 1. Heap init
4\~MB heap at physical 16\~MB.  Must complete before any println! or allocation.
.TP
.B 2. UEFI framebuffer init
UEFI GOP mapped; 8\(mu16 Hebrew bitmap font rendered natively on framebuffer.
.TP
.B 3. Interrupt init
IDT loaded, 8259 PIC configured.  IRQ0 (timer) and IRQ1 (keyboard) unmasked.
This is the symmetry-breaking event (\(*F_\(+- \(-> \(*F_asym).
.TP
.B 4. Subsystem validation
Three-layer objects, scheduler, memory, filesystem, IPC, command grammar \(em
all structural/operational/determinative variants exercised.
.TP
.B 5. ALEPH system online
22-letter type system loaded.  Tier census: O_\(if:3, O_2:6, O_1:1, O_0:12.
Three Frobenius fixed points verified by assertion.
.TP
.B 6. Type-gate verification
All five type gates tested with
.BR assert!() .
Conscience scores printed.
.TP
.B 7. Holographic monitor spawn
.B holographic_monitor_entry
allocated a real 16\~KB kernel stack and queued as process 1000.
.TP
.B 8. Timer registration
.B scheduler::register_for_timer()
wires the global scheduler to the PIT IRQ0 handler.
Symmetry broken: holographic monitor eligible for scheduling.
.TP
.B 9. ALFS mount
ATA primary slave (alfs.img, 32\~MB).  Programs seeded from kernel binary if absent.
.TP
.B 10. Shell
Interactive prompt
.BR "exOS>" .
.
