.SH IMASM VM
The
.B IMASM
(Imscribing Grammar Assembly) VM is a Tri-Phase Flux Register machine with four register states:
Void, True, False, Both (quantum superposition).
.PP
Four undeciphered script systems are compiled to IMASM opcodes:
.TP
.B Voynich
.br
.B "imasm voynich ch sh o p e a d s t k r y"
(EVA character scan codes)
.TP
.B Rohonc Codex
.br
.B "imasm rohonc cr hk fa ba lg lp br cv vt hz cl dt"
(RTFF two-char scan codes)
.TP
.B Linear A
.br
.B "imasm linear-a cu hk fa ba lt lp br cv vt hz cl dt"
(LATFF two-char scan codes)
.TP
.B Emerald Tablet
.br
.B "imasm emerald-tablet tr an as ds lk id sp un af ng px fx"
(ETFF two-char scan codes)
.PP
The Emerald Tablet is the only compiled manuscript with both type gates open and C\~=\~1.0.
