.SH DIAGNOSTICS
.TP
.B [BOOT] Heap: initialized (4MB)
Heap is ready.  All subsequent boot steps may allocate.
.TP
.B [SCHED] Ergative scheduler online, symmetry broken
Scheduler initialized; symmetry-breaking event (first interrupt) has fired.
.TP
.B [TYPE] IPC gate (close): accepted=true
The IPC distance gate is operational and passing close-type messages.
.TP
.B [TYPE] Ω gate (Velar+User): allowed=false
User objects correctly rejected from kernel-depth allocation.
.TP
.B [HOLO] Holographic monitor (g(x)): spawn ok=true
g(x) process passed all five spawn gates and has a live 16\~KB kernel stack.
.TP
.B [g(x)] iter=N LCARD=M REFL=false radius=R
The holographic monitor is actually running on the CPU, not just queued.
Printed every 64 iterations of its main loop.
.TP
.B KERNEL PANIC
Unrecoverable fault.  CPU halts.  Connect serial to see the panic message.
.
.SH NOTES
exoterik_OS runs in ring-0 only.  No user/kernel mode transition, no syscall interface,
no paging beyond what UEFI provides.  Processes are cooperative (they yield explicitly
or via the preemption flag); there is no forced preemption from interrupt context.
.PP
The maximum number of real processes is bounded by MAX_PROCS\~=\~32 (RSP_TABLE slots)
and MAX_ENTRIES\~=\~128 (ALFS directory).
.PP
Ħ (primitive index 9) denotes
.B chirality
\(em not "temporal depth" or any other label.
